From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 11:51:05 +0200
Subject: net: stmmac: dwmac-tc956x: add shutdown callback to quiesce the MAC

The 2.5G MAC on the Q8B sits behind a TC956x (QPS615) PCIe switch. On an
orderly shutdown or reboot the platform can power down the PCIe link
before the eMAC is quiesced; a later MDIO MMIO access over the dead bus
stalls on the PCIe NoC and hangs the board. The auxiliary driver has no
shutdown handler, so its DMA engine and PHY polling stay live until power
is removed. Add a .shutdown callback that runs stmmac_suspend() to stop
the DMA engine, mask the interrupts and park the PHY before the bus goes
away. A suspend failure is only logged, since shutdown must proceed.

Signed-off-by: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c | 16 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c
@@ -801,6 +801,21 @@ static void tc956x_dwmac_remove(struct auxiliary_device *adev)
 	of_node_put(td->plat->mdio_node);
 }
 
+/*
+ * Quiesce the DMA engine and park the PHY before the PCIe link is powered
+ * down, so no MDIO access is issued over the dead bus and the board can
+ * reboot cleanly.
+ */
+static void tc956x_dwmac_shutdown(struct auxiliary_device *adev)
+{
+	struct device *dev = &adev->dev;
+	int ret;
+
+	ret = stmmac_suspend(dev);
+	if (ret)
+		dev_warn(dev, "failed to suspend MAC during shutdown: %d\n", ret);
+}
+
 static const struct auxiliary_device_id tc956x_dwmac_ids[] = {
 	{ .name = TC956X_PCIE_DRIVER_NAME "." TC956X_XGMAC_DEV_NAME, },
 	{ },
@@ -811,6 +826,7 @@ static struct auxiliary_driver tc956x_dwmac_driver = {
 	.name		= DRIVER_NAME,
 	.probe		= tc956x_dwmac_probe,
 	.remove		= tc956x_dwmac_remove,
+	.shutdown	= tc956x_dwmac_shutdown,
 	.id_table	= tc956x_dwmac_ids,
 	.driver = {
 		.name	= DRIVER_NAME,
-- 
